# ============================================================================
# _dayz-server-manager — zsh completion for the DayZ server installer/watchdog
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/mr-guard/dayz-server-manager
#   Author     : mr-guard
#   License    : MIT
#   Stars      : 206
#   Language   : TypeScript
#   npm        : dayz-server-manager
#   Binary     : dayz-server-manager  (package.json bin → dist/index.js)
#   Last push  : 2025-02-26
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   dayz-server-manager is "a server installer and watch-dog for DayZ
#   standalone with built-in Discord and RCon bot" — mr-guard's Node.js
#   daemon for the DayZ Standalone dedicated-server workflow.  On
#   startup the manager performs a requirements check (Steam tools / DayZ
#   server binaries), updates the base server install + workshop mods
#   via SteamCMD, launches the DayZ server process under supervision,
#   and exposes management surfaces:
#     - a discord.js Discord bot listening for slash commands
#     - an RCon bot for in-game admin commands
#     - a built-in Express web UI for browser-side server administration
#     - a scheduled-events runner (auto-restart, scheduled messages,
#       periodic mod-update checks, etc.)
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/index.ts helpText constant +
#                       process.argv.includes() flag checks)
#   dayz-server-manager [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     --help            Show the help text and exit
#     --skip-init       Skip the init process (requirements check,
#                       server update, mod update)
#     --start-locked    Activate the server restart lock so the
#                       manager does NOT start the DayZ server when
#                       it boots
#     --skip-events     Skip execution of scheduled events (restart
#                       timers, broadcasts, mod-refresh cron entries)
#
#   Behavior:
#     - All other configuration lives in the YAML / JSON config file
#       referenced by the working directory's `manager.yaml` (or
#       overridable via env);  no further CLI flags are accepted.
#     - On Windows when launched from the GUI the process pauses on
#       exit (via spawnSync 'pause') so the user can read errors.
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `discord.js` declared in package.json
#   `"dependencies"` — the canonical Node.js Discord library
#   (discordjs/discord.js, the de-facto Discord API binding used by the
#   vast majority of Node.js Discord bots).  dayz-server-manager uses
#   discord.js for the in-game-admin Discord bot, channeling server
#   events (restarts / crashes / mod updates / RCon admin actions) into
#   a configured Discord guild, and accepting reciprocal slash commands
#   to drive RCon admin operations from chat.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/mr-guard/dayz-server-manager/contents/package.json
#       → "discord.js" in "dependencies"
#   This entry is the TS-Node=122 leader bump that CLOSES Axis 67
#   (Discord Bot Library) at 1/1/1 three-language symmetry:
#     Rust   = serenity 0.12.1 + poise 0.6.1  (R857, `displex`, mchestr)
#     Go     = bwmarrin/discordgo v0.29.0      (R858, `pingme`,  kha7iq)
#     TS-Node = discord.js                     (R859, `dayz-server-manager`,
#                                                       mr-guard)
#   Reaches the triple-122 landmark Rust=Go=TS-Node=122 *and* the
#   THREE-SCORE 60-AXES round-number landmark (60 axes at 1/1/1
#   three-language symmetry).
#
#   No completion for `dayz-server-manager` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_dayz-server-manager() {
    _arguments \
        '(- *)--help[show help and exit]' \
        '--skip-init[skip init process (requirements check, server update, mod update)]' \
        '--start-locked[activate server restart lock; do not start DayZ server on manager boot]' \
        '--skip-events[skip execution of scheduled events]'
}

_dayz-server-manager "$@"
